# Mandatory AI Development Plugins

**IMPORTANT:** At the start of EVERY new project or first session in a workspace, verify these 3 plugins are installed and configured.

## Quick Verification Checklist

```
[ ] claude-mem - Worker running, context rule exists
[ ] code-simplifier - Plugin folder exists in .cursor/plugins/
[ ] superpowers - Documented in CLAUDE.md (Claude Code CLI plugin)
```

---

## 1. Claude-Mem (Persistent Memory)

Provides persistent memory across AI coding sessions. Automatically captures tool usage, file edits, and shell commands.

### Verify Installation

```bash
# Check worker is running
curl -s http://127.0.0.1:37777/api/readiness
# Expected: {"status":"ready","mcpReady":true}

# Check project is registered
curl -s http://127.0.0.1:37777/api/projects
```

### Project Configuration Required

Each project needs:
1. **Context rule file:** `.cursor/rules/claude-mem-context.mdc`
2. **Context populated:** Should show recent observations, not "No previous sessions"

### Fix Missing Context

```bash
# Refresh context for a project
PROJECT="project-name"
curl -s "http://127.0.0.1:37777/api/context/inject?project=${PROJECT}" > .cursor/rules/claude-mem-context.mdc
```

### Start Worker (if not running)

```bash
cd ~/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/thedotmack && bun run worker:start
```

